docs.abstract: China is heavily reliant on imported computer chips, despite efforts to develop its own semiconductor industry.

docs.lead_paragraph: BEIJING — For all of China’s efforts to become a global force in high technology rivaling the United States, it has mostly failed to produce top-flight contenders in one crucial area: the industry that gave Silicon Valley its name.
